commit.message: Bump PV to 0.2.1.
Add expansion functions.
Use the complete set of args to AC_INIT.
Bump PV to 0.2.

Region 2: make cp, cv, w(p, T) compatible with fill_powers().

By design, it is necessary to enforce that k-th and (k+1)-th exponents
are k & k+1, where k is the derivative number. For the second
derivative, this means that Jpows[2] == 2 & Jpows[3] == 3.
Enable debug (assertions) in distcheck.
h2o_t: support getting cp, cv, w.
Region 4: cp, cv, w(T,x).
Region 3: cp, cv, w(rho,T).
Region 5: cp, cv, w(p,T).

Region 2/meta: cp, cv, w(p,T).

Right now, values are incorrect due to a bug in twoarg_poly_value().
Add helpful debugging code to twoarg_poly_value().
Move not_reached into consts.h.
Region 2: cp, cv, w(p,T).
poly_value(): support second (and likely more) derivatives.
Region 1: cv(p,T) & w(p,T).
Drop unit comments from function decls.
xmath: add assertions for supported derivative range.
Region 1: cp(p, T).
xmath: twoarg_poly_value(), support getting second derivative.
Inline pi/tau/delta subexpressions in property getters.
Bump PV to 0.1.
Add NEWS generation rule.
Add minimalistic API docs to h2o.h.
Introduce a simple README.
h2o_t: treat unsupported R5(p,h), (p,s) & (h,s) as out-of-range.

Split out most of xmath functions into non-inline forms.

The benefit of having them inline is negligable yet library is 100 KiB
smaller without that.
Header files: wrap (very long) region getting functions.
Region 3: header file line wrapping.
Region 3: group functions alike in header.
